M||tx|---
M|Lang|it|ts strict mode where applicable
M|Lang|it|No `any` tp unless absolutely necessary — add a comment explaining why
M|Lang|it|Prefer explicit return tp on all functions
M|Lang|it|Use `const` by default; `let` only when reassignment is required
M|Func|it|Keep functions small and single-purpose
M|Func|it|Max 30 lines per fn; extract if longer
M|Func|it|Name functions after what they return, not what they do internally
M|Func|it|No side effects in pure functions
M|Erro|it|Never swallow er silently
M|Erro|it|Always log er context, not just the er message
M|Erro|it|Use typed er where possible
M|Comm|it|Comment the why, not the what
M|Comm|it|If code needs a comment to be understood, consider simplifying it first
M|Comm|it|Never leave TODO comments w/o a ticket reference
M|File|it|One concern per file
M|File|it|Keep files under 200 lines; split if larger
M|File|it|Co-locate tests w/ implementation files
M|Git|it|All br changes go to `dv` branch — never commit directly to `main`
M|Git|- Co|`tp(scope): short description` (feat, fix, chore, doc)